🚌 The road always gives me a wealth of memories. Singing Here Comes The Sun with the crowd in Liverpool, staying up late enough for my first Gossip Hour 🤫 on the @sophieellisbextor band bus, ending up in a hospital in Leeds at 2.30am with Oyster 🦪 poisoning, puking on a bus fanging down a highway, meeting fans for the first time I had no idea I had or old fans who’ve bought merch for years for the first time. Huge thanks to Sophie and her truly great touring family and sequin clad fans, who I love so much and take me in as their own. I feel so lucky and honoured and cherished every moment !! I nearly took a job as a croupier at an online crypto Casino where I’d be wearing a playboy bunny suit 😂 and turned it down an hour before Sophie messaged me with the offer. I nearly gave up earlier this year too and I’m so so deeply grateful for every moment I get to keep making music and performing, especially when it’s with the most amazing pop star and person ⭐️ Ms Sophie. Big thanks to my hubby too for having my back and holding the fort. Hope I get to see more of you all in 2024 with this new record I’ve put so much into ❤️‍🔥🩷🫶🩷❤️‍🔥 keeping the flame burning… xx Holiday
